All Kajiado county revenue officers yesterday were suspended or sent on compulsory leave in connection with suspected irregular spending.  First to exit was director of Revenue in the Finance department, followed by all five subcounty revenue officers in Kajiado East, Kajiado South, Kajiado West, Kajiado Central and Kajiado North constituencies.  Governor Joseph ole Lenku made the announcement yesterday. He said taxpayers’ money has been going into individuals pockets at the expense of development.  He appointed David Montet, Vera Moraa and Janet Sereu as directors of Licensing and Permits, Compliance and Enforcement of Revenue and User Fees and Sales Revenue, respectively.  He appointed Leah Sankaire  Chief of Protocol. Rachael Shibaiira replaced her as  Chief of Staff.  